Q1. What is perceptron learning algorithm?
A supervised learning algorithm used for binary classification that updates weights based on prediction error.

Q2. What is decision boundary?
A line or hyperplane separating different classes in feature space.

Q3. What is learning rate?
Learning rate controls magnitude of weight updates.

Q4. Why use activation function?
To decide neuron output based on weighted sum.

Q5. What is linearly separable data?
Data that can be separated using a straight line.

Q6. Why perceptron fails for XOR?
Because XOR is non-linearly separable.

